deck: John Orlando began as a penciling assistant to Rich Buckler in 1994 for Buckler's Visage Studios and became Production Manager at Visage in 1995. John produced several creator-owned books in 1996-98 including the off-beat 'classic style' titles Cybergen, Journey into Madness, The Intruder, and a co-owned property with Roy Thomas, Doc Behemoth. Upon his comeback, he produced four issues, an annual, and a mini special of his Underground Comix title FHA-Q, from 2012-2013.
name: John Orlando
